PN,37702
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F377A1782323307
OL,3,CStorms cause floods and big travel
OL,4,Cdisruption across London
OL,6,FA foot of moving water at just 6mph is
OL,7,Fenough to float a car.
OL,9,FAssistant Commissioner Pat Goulbourne
OL,10,Fsaid: "It has been a very busy night
OL,11,Ffor our Control Officers, firefighters
OL,12,Fand officers. Shortly after 0400 hrs,
OL,13,Fdue to a large number of calls
OL,14,Freceived by the Brigade, we
OL,15,Fimplemented our High-Volume Call
OL,16,Fprocedure which means flooding calls
OL,17,Fwhere there is a risk to life are
OL,18,Fprioritised and crews then attend
OL,19,Fother calls as non-emergencies when
OL,20,Fthey can.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G2/5
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,378,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37703
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F377A1782323307
OL,3,CStorms cause floods and big travel
OL,4,Cdisruption across London
OL,6,F"Operation Willow Beck was also
OL,7,Ftemporarily stood up. Introduced in
OL,8,F2022 nationally by the Home Office and
OL,9,FNational Chiefs Fire Council, this is
OL,10,Fa pre-determined 999 call distribution
OL,11,Fprocedure, which during times of
OL,12,Fextreme demand, can divert surplus
OL,13,Femergency calls to unaffected fire and
OL,14,Frescue service control rooms. I'd like
OL,15,Fto thank all of those colleagues in
OL,16,Fother fire rescue services who
OL,17,Fassisted us overnight, as well as our
OL,18,Fown staff for their hard work and
OL,19,Fprofessionalism during this busy
OL,20,Fperiod.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G3/5
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,378,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37704
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F377A1782323307
OL,3,CStorms cause floods and big travel
OL,4,Cdisruption across London
OL,6,F"Whilst the worst of the rain now
OL,7,Fseems to have passed, we continue to
OL,8,Fwork through outstanding calls as well
OL,9,Fas receive new incidents as Londoners
OL,10,Fwake to see some of the damage caused
OL,11,Fby the storms overnight.
OL,13,F"We'd like to reassure Londoners that
OL,14,Fcrews are available to respond to
OL,15,Femergencies so please call 999 if you
OL,16,Fhave to."
OL,18,FAdvice from the London Fire Brigade
OL,19,Fsays:
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G4/5
